"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020826","Department for International Development","false","2018-12-14","<p>We are deeply concerned by continued lack of access and reports of violence in Kachin and also northern Shan States, which has led to a further 8,000 people being displaced since February 2018. The UK continues to push for unfettered access at every given opportunity. Most recently, the British Ambassador raised the importance of ensuring humanitarian access in his meeting with the Chief Minister of Kachin State on 3 December.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-12-14T15:35:08.127Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020826/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020826/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020826/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-12-07","Burma: Humanitarian Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent assessment her Department has made of the level of access by providers of humanitarian aid to (a) Kachin and (b) Shan State in Burma.","false","Biography information for Stephen Twigg","Liverpool, West Derby","Stephen Twigg","200074"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020827","Department for International Development","false","2018-12-12","<p>The UK government is deeply concerned about the findings of the IMPACT-se report into the Palestinian Authority’s (PA) new curriculum and it remains a priority for the Development for International Development (DFID) to commission an independent review of the PA’s textbooks. We are also continuing to raise our concerns about incitement, which the Minister did himself at a meeting with the Palestinian Education Minister earlier this year. Last week, on 4<sup>th</sup> December, DFID officials met the PA Minister for Education and raised UK concerns over specific examples in the IMPACT-SE report.</p><p> </p><p>Our timeline for the textbook review remains unchanged. We will complete the review by September 2019. The UK has been convening discussions with potential international partners on commissioning the review together, in order to increase the impact of the study. We will commission the review in the new year once we have concluded these discussions. We will publish further information once the assessment has been commissioned.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-12-12T17:14:38.703Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020827/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020827/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020827/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-12-07","Palestinians: Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development,  pursuant to the Answer of 12 September 2018 to Question 171641 on Palestinians: Schools, whether her Department has commissioned the study into the new Palestinian textbooks.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","200063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020828","Department for Transport","false","2018-12-12","<p>Ministers and officials from the Department for Transport have regular discussions with the Mayor of London, representatives of the London Assembly and Transport for London covering a variety of subjects including rail services in London.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2018-12-12T13:25:40.86Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020828/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020828/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020828/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-12-07","Great Northern Railway Line: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with the Mayor of London on transferring franchising authority to Transport for London for contracting Great Northern metro train services that run to and from Moorgate station.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","200064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020829","Department for Transport","false","2018-12-12","<p>Building on the Strategic Vision for Rail, the Department is actively considering the future of the TSGN franchise. It is doing this working closely with the Williams Rail Review, which, as part of its work, is examining the most appropriate organisational and commercial models for the future railway. This work is at an early stage and nothing is off the table.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2018-12-12T13:00:55.2Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020829/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020829/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020829/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-12-07","Govia Thameslink Railway: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to transfer commuter rail services to Transport for London as proposed in Chris Gibb's independent report to the Department for Transport on the Govia Thameslink Railway franchise.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","200065"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020830","Department for Transport","false","2018-12-12","<p>Ministers and officials from the Department for Transport have regular discussions with the Mayor of London, representatives of the London Assembly and Transport for London covering a variety of subjects including rail services in London.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2018-12-12T13:13:40.437Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020830/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020830/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020830/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-12-07","Railways: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many meetings he has had with the Mayor of London on plans for devolving commuter rail services to Transport for London.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","200066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020831","Department for Transport","false","2018-12-12","<p>The Department has concluded that the disruption on this network was caused by a series of mistakes and complex issues across the rail industry. This is in line with Professor Stephen Glaister’s interim report.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is holding GTR to account for their role in the unacceptable performance following the introduction of the May timetable. To this end, GTR will make no profit from its franchise in this financial year. Looking ahead, we have also capped the amount of profit that the operator is able to make for the remainder of its franchise, which is due to expire in September 2021.</p><p> </p><p>Furthermore, GTR will be contributing £15m towards tangible improvements for passengers. This is in addition to the £15m the operator has already contributed towards compensation for passengers since the May timetable disruption.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2018-12-12T13:21:16.183Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020831/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020831/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020831/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-12-07","Govia Thameslink Railway: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has completed its hard review of the Govia Thameslink Railway franchise; and if he will make statement.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","200067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020832","Treasury","false","2018-12-17","<p>UK Government departments have not been set budgets beyond the current Spending Review period. The Barnett Formula will be applied in the normal way at the next Spending Review to the additional allocations to the Ministry for Housing, Communities and Local Government.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-12-17T12:54:31.387Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020832/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020832/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020832/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-12-07","Housing Associations: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 11 October 2018 to Question 176223 on Housing Associations: Finance, whether that new spending will result in Barnett consequentials for the devolved administrations.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","200107"
