"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020647","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-12-12","<p>As of 9 November, the Department of Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) led on 46 EU legislative files that remain under negotiation.</p><p> </p><p>It is not possible to say which files will be implemented in UK law; this will depend on a range of factors including the nature of any future EU-UK relationship and the details of the final agreed texts of individual files including any transposition deadlines.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst",,"2018-12-12T16:49:28.673Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020647/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020647/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020647/answer","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020647/answer/previousversion/91431","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-12-06","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many in-flight files of EU legislation exist that affect the policy areas managed by his Department; and which in-flight files of EU legislation his Department intends to implement in UK law.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","199838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020648","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-12-13","<p>During the time-limited implementation period, EU law will continue to apply in the UK subject to the terms set out in the Withdrawal Agreement.</p><p> </p><p>The MOJ currently has two in-flight files being managed within the department which may require implementation during any agreed Implementation Period. This is without prejudice to other live files currently in-flight in the EU over which the UK may seek a post-adoption opt-in.</p><p> </p><p>The Official Journal of the European Union publishes upcoming EU legislation for implementation. This is publicly available online: <a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/oj/direct-access.html" target="_blank">https://eur-lex.europa.eu/oj/direct-access.html</a> .</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-12-13T16:08:50.327Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020648/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020648/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-12-06","Ministry of Justice: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many in-flight files of EU legislation exist that effect the policy areas managed by his Department; and which in-flight files of EU legislation his Department intends to implement in UK law.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","199839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020649","Home Office","false","2018-12-13","<p>The Home Office is participating in ongoing negotiations on 25 EU legislative files. Of those, the UK will only be bound by 9 files as a result of the UK’s ability to not opt in or opt out under the UK’s JHA and Schengen Protocols respectively. Until the UK leaves the EU, and during the proposed Implementation Period, the UK is required to give effect to these measures, once agreed by the EU.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-12-13T15:22:04.517Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020649/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020649/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-12-06","Home Office: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many in-flight files of EU legislation exist that effect the policy areas managed by his Department; and which in-flight files of EU legislation his Department intends to implement in UK law.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","199840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020650","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-12-14","<p>The UK remains a member of the EU until we leave, with full rights and obligations of membership. This includes transposing EU legislation into UK law. During the time-limited implementation period, EU law will continue to apply in the UK subject to the terms set out in the Withdrawal Agreement.</p><p> </p><p>After the implementation period, all laws in the UK will be passed by our elected representatives in Belfast, Cardiff, Edinburgh and London. The Political Declaration recognises that the UK may choose to align with the EU’s rules in relevant areas to facilitate trade in goods or security cooperation.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-12-14T11:17:03.683Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020650/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020650/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1020650/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-12-06","Department for Work and Pensions: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many in-flight files of EU legislation exist that effect the policy areas managed by her Department; and which in-flight files of EU legislation his Department intends to implement in UK law.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","199841"
